cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with text-to-SQL generation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the purview of cs.CL. 
2. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper proposes a self-attention based database schema encoder to address the Spider dataset, which involves complex queries over multiple tables. This makes it relevant to the field of databases. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a deep learning approach for text-to-SQL generation, which is a subfield of AI. 
4. cs.LG (Learning) - The paper proposes a neural architecture for text-to-SQL generation, which involves training a model to learn from data. This makes it relevant to the field of machine learning and falls under cs.LG. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with generating SQL queries from natural language text, which is a task that involves retrieving relevant information from a database. This makes it relevant to the field of information retrieval.
